Google has released the results of its 2019 Year in Search, which outlines the biggest trends based on searches conducted in South Africa over the past year. Trending searches showed South Africa’s interest in load-shedding, Black Friday, local celebrities, and news and events, with nine of the top 10 trending search terms being related to local matters. The top sports searches were dominated by the Rugby and Cricket World Cup, and the most-searched-for question on Google in South Africa over the last year was “Why were cornflakes invented?”. Other popular search trends over the past decade included Meghan Markle, Game of Thrones, Thanos, and Uzalo. Below are the top trending searches in South Africa for 2019.